name: $::type
desc: Returns: Indicates what a category of item that was consumed: eg., food, fluid, enteral, etc.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indicates what a category of item that was consumed: eg., food, fluid, enteral, etc.

name: $nutritionProduct
desc: Returns: Identifies the food or fluid product that was consumed. This is potentially a link to a resource representing the details of the food product (TBD) or a simple attribute carrying a code that identifies the food from a known list of foods.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identifies the food or fluid product that was consumed. This is potentially a link to a resource representing the details of the food product (TBD) or a simple attribute carrying a code that identifies the food from a known list of foods.

name: $amount
desc: Returns: Quantity of the specified food.

name: $rate
desc: Returns: Rate at which enteral feeding was administered.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Rate at which enteral feeding was administered.

name: $notConsumed
desc: Returns: Indicator when a patient is in a setting where it is helpful to know if food was not consumed, such as it was refused, held (as in tube feedings), or otherwise not provided. If a consumption is being recorded from an app, such as MyFitnessPal, this indicator will likely not be used.

name: $notConsumedReason
desc: Returns: Document the reason the food or fluid was not consumed, such as refused, held, etc.
